OL,6,FAbbington said she would like the BBC
OL,7,Fto make a public apology if their
OL,8,Freview finds there is a case to
OL,9,Fanswer, but adds that she has had no
OL,10,Fcontact with anyone senior at the
OL,11,Fcorporation since the scandal erupted.
OL,13,FA BBC spokesperson said: "Anyone
OL,14,Finvolved in a complaint has a right to
OL,15,Fconfidentiality and fair process and
OL,16,Ftherefore it would be inappropriate to
OL,17,Fcomment further on individuals.
