OL,6,FRight now that means a part in a play
OL,7,Fdealing with the aftermath of trauma,
OL,8,Fand the need to find your voice and
OL,9,Fspeak out.
OL,11,FShe signed up for the When It Happens
OL,12,FTo You production before she agreed to
OL,13,FStrictly. That empowerment is a theme
OL,14,Fin that, and in what she wants other
OL,15,Fwomen to have if they too have
OL,16,Fconcerns, is a strange coincidence.
OL,18,FIt is unclear as yet when the BBC
OL,19,Finvestigation will be complete, but
OL,20,FAmanda Abbington is waiting.
